    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nVim options have very specific behavior for the way they can be modified, e.g. with `:set foo ^= bar` to prepend, `+=` to append, `-=` to remove. And https://github.com/vim/vim/pull/19783 will further enhance this behavior.\n\n`runtime/lua/vim/_core/options.lua` appears to reimplement this functionality : https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/256811a617cbe97aa1dd2b3eef3b69b90608d54c/runtime/lua/vim/_core/options.lua#L424-L446\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLet `nvim_set_option_value` take a new `operation: 'append'|'prepend'|'remove'` key (name TBD) which leverages the existing internal options manipulation functionality.\n\nDrop the duplicate implementation in `runtime/lua/vim/_core/options.lua`.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
